nodes.bodyText:
If an SCI is being run on a ServletContextHandler, there's no expectations of bytecode scanning (IMO).
It would be sweet if we could just do ...
ServletContextHandler handler = new ServletContextHandler();
handler.addBean(new MyLibServletContextInitializer());
handler.addBean(new org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.EnhancedListener()); // this is an SCI
server.setHandler(handler);
server.start(); // this loads the SCI's from the beans and uses them.
Just have ServletContextHandler be aware of SCI as beans and load / call them with no/empty classes.
Or, if this raw/naked SCI as bean concept isn't right, how about a specific call on ServletContextHandler for them?
ServletContextHandler handler = new ServletContextHandler();
handler.addInitializer(new MyLibServletContextInitializer(), Collections.emptySet());
handler.addInitializer(new org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.EnhancedListener(), Collections.emptySet());
server.setHandler(handler);
server.start();

